              <li>Mortgage documents for bank</li>
              <li>Title deed for records</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="comparison-col">
            <h4>Renting Property</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="/legal/contracts/lease/">Tenancy contract</a> for Ejari</li>
              <li>Ejari certificate for visa</li>
              <li>DEWA connection letter</li>
              <li>Landlord NOC if needed</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>Employment and Visa Documentation</h3>
        <p>Marina residents work across Dubai. Many commute to <a href="/locations/dubai/difc/">DIFC</a>, <a href="/locations/dubai/business-bay/">Business Bay</a>, or Media City. Employment changes mean visa changes, which mean translation needs. New jobs require degree attestation and translation. Salary certificates need translation for various applications.</p>

        <p>Common employment-related translations include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong><a href="/personal/academic/degree/">University degrees</a>:</strong> For MOHRE credential verification</li>
          <li><strong>Employment contracts:</strong> For visa processing and disputes</li>
          <li><strong><a href="/personal/immigration/bank/">Salary certificates</a>:</strong> For loan applications and family visa</li>
          <li><strong>Experience letters:</strong> For job applications and licensing</li>
          <li><strong><a href="/personal/immigration/pcc/">Police clearance</a>:</strong> For visa renewals and new employment</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Family Documentation Needs</h3>
        <p>Marina families need translation for the milestones of expatriate life. Children need <a href="/personal/vital-records/birth/">birth certificate translation</a> for school enrollment and passport applications. <a href="/personal/vital-records/marriage/">Marriage certificates</a> must be translated for spouse visa sponsorship. When family circumstances change, <a href="/personal/vital-records/divorce/">divorce decrees</a> need translation for legal proceedings.</p>

        <div class="process-breakdown">
          <h4>School Enrollment</h4>
          <p>Marina schools—GEMS, Nord Anglia, and others—typically require translated birth certificates and previous school records for enrollment. Some require translated parent identification documents.</p>

          <h4>Family Visa Sponsorship</h4>
          <p>Sponsoring family members requires translated marriage certificates, birth certificates, and relationship proof. GDRFA accepts our MOJ-certified translations for all family visa applications.</p>

          <h4>Medical Situations</h4>
          <p>Medical emergencies sometimes require translated <a href="/specialized/medical/">medical records</a> from home countries. Insurance claims may need translated hospital documentation.</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Business Owners in Marina</h3>
        <p>Many Marina residents run businesses. Some operate from <a href="/locations/dubai/jlt/">nearby JLT</a> free zone offices. Others have mainland companies or work as consultants. Business documentation needs include:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><a href="/legal/corporate/moa/">MOA translation</a> for bank account opening</li>
          <li><a href="/legal/corporate/resolution/">Board resolutions</a> for signatory changes</li>
          <li><a href="/legal/contracts/">Commercial contracts</a> for business dealings</li>
          <li><a href="/specialized/financial/">Financial statements</a> for loan applications</li>
          <li><a href="/legal/corporate/poa/">Powers of Attorney</a> for remote management</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Common Mistakes Marina Residents Make</h3>

