            <h4>Which Marina schools accept your translated documents?</h4>
            <p>All Marina-area schools including GEMS Wellington International, Dubai British School, and Nord Anglia accept our MOJ-certified translations for enrollment documentation. We translate <a href="/personal/vital-records/birth/">birth certificates</a>, previous school records, and <a href="/personal/academic/transcripts/">academic transcripts</a> in formats schools require.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h4>Can you collect documents from my Marina tower?</h4>
            <p>Yes. We offer complimentary pickup from any Marina address. Our courier can collect original documents from your tower concierge or directly from you. For urgent requests, we recommend WhatsApp submission of document photos for immediate processing, with originals collected afterward if needed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h4>How do I translate documents for Ejari registration?</h4>
            <p>Ejari registration for Marina rentals requires a translated <a href="/legal/contracts/lease/">tenancy contract</a> if the original is not in Arabic. We provide Ejari-ready translations that include all required fields and formatting. Most tenancy contracts complete within 4-6 hours.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h4>What if my documents are in a language other than English?</h4>
            <p>We translate directly from the source language to Arabic without intermediate English translation. Common languages in Marina include Hindi, Urdu, Russian, Chinese, French, German, and Spanish. Direct translation preserves accuracy and legal terminology from the original document.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
